To display only even numbers, an `if` statement can be added inside the `for` loop to check if the current number `num` is even using the modulo operator (`%`).

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main() {
    int minNumber, maxNumber;
    std::cout << "I will display a table of even numbers and "
              << "their squares.\n";
    std::cout << "Enter the starting number: ";
